## Answer

### 1. How pi extensions register tools (`registerTool` API)

**Two patterns:**

**Pattern A — Inline (simple):**
```typescript
pi.registerTool({
  name: "greet",
  label: "Greet",
  description: "Greet someone by name",
  parameters: Type.Object({
    name: Type.String({ description: "Name to greet" }),
  }),
  async execute(toolCallId, params, signal, onUpdate, ctx) {
    return {
      content: [{ type: "text", text: `Hello, ${params.name}!` }],
      details: {},
    };
  },
});
```

**Pattern B — `defineTool` helper (recommended):**
```typescript
import { defineTool, type ExtensionAPI } from "@earendil-works/pi-coding-agent";
import { Type } from "typebox";

const helloTool = defineTool({
  name: "hello",
  label: "Hello",
  description: "A simple greeting tool",
  parameters: Type.Object({
    name: Type.String({ description: "Name to greet" }),
  }),
  async execute(_toolCallId, params, _signal, _onUpdate, _ctx) {
    return {
      content: [{ type: "text", text: `Hello, ${params.name}!` }],
      details: { greeted: params.name },
    };
  },
});

export default function (pi: ExtensionAPI) {
  pi.registerTool(helloTool);
}
```

**`execute` signature:**
```
async execute(toolCallId, params, signal, onUpdate, ctx) → { content, details, isError? }
```
- `onUpdate` — stream partial results: `onUpdate?.({ content: [{ type: "text", text: "Working..." }] })`
- `signal` — AbortSignal for cancellation
- `params` — typed from your Typebox schema
- Return `{ content: ContentPart[], details: Record<string, unknown>, isError?: boolean }`

**Optional fields on tool definition:**
- `promptSnippet` — one-line entry in "Available tools"
- `promptGuidelines` — tool-specific bullets for Guidelines section
- `prepareArguments(args)` — pre-validation compatibility shim
- `renderCall` / `renderResult` — custom TUI rendering

**`registerTool` works any time** — during load, inside `session_start`, or in event handlers. New tools appear immediately without `/reload`.

---

### 2. CloakBrowser's JS API (Playwright-based)

**Install:**
```bash
npm install cloakbrowser playwright-core
```

**Core API:**
```javascript
import { launch, launchContext, launchPersistentContext } from 'cloakbrowser';
```

**`launch()` — returns Playwright `Browser`:**
```javascript
const browser = await launch();  // headless, default stealth

const browser = await launch({
  headless: false,                                    // headed mode
  proxy: 'http://user:pass@proxy:8080',              // HTTP/SOCKS5 proxy
  args: ['--fingerprint=12345'],                      // custom Chromium flags
  timezone: 'America/New_York',                       // set timezone
  locale: 'en-US',                                    // set locale
  geoip: true,                                        // auto-detect tz/locale from proxy
  humanize: true,                                     // human-like mouse/keyboard/scroll
  humanPreset: 'careful',                             // slower, more deliberate
  stealthArgs: false,                                 // disable default stealth args
});
```

**Navigate & get content (standard Playwright API):**
```javascript
const page = await browser.newPage();
await page.goto('https://example.com');
const title = await page.title();
const html = await page.content();
const text = await page.locator('body').textContent();
await browser.close();
```

**`launchContext()` — browser + context in one call:**
```javascript
const context = await launchContext({
  userAgent: 'Custom UA',
  viewport: { width: 1920, height: 1080 },
  locale: 'en-US',
  timezone: 'America/New_York',
});
const page = await context.newPage();
await page.goto('https://example.com');
await context.close();
```

**`launchPersistentContext()` — cookies/localStorage survive restarts:**
```javascript
const ctx = await launchPersistentContext({
  userDataDir: './chrome-profile',
  headless: false,
  proxy: 'http://user:pass@proxy:8080',
});
const page = await ctx.newPage();
await page.goto('https://example.com');
await ctx.close();
```

**Utility functions:**
```javascript
import { ensureBinary, clearCache, binaryInfo } from 'cloakbrowser';
await ensureBinary();    // pre-download binary
console.log(binaryInfo()); // { version, platform, installed, ... }
```

**Key point:** CloakBrowser returns standard Playwright objects — all Playwright methods work: `newPage()`, `newContext()`, `page.goto()`, `page.content()`, `page.title()`, `page.locator()`, `page.evaluate()`, etc.

